issue.body:
Kibana version: 8.12

Currently, when trying to export large number of rules, 500 error is displayed on UI and no error logged within Kibana

<img width="2552" alt="Screenshot 2023-10-27 at 11 58 12" src="https://github.com/elastic/security-team/assets/92328789/fcd2ace5-c644-4d3d-9a85-ad0f5d32bbd9">

When looked into sent requests on server side, I been able to find the cause of the issue:

ES request failed with error

```JSON

{
  "error": {
    "root_cause": [
      {
        "type": "too_many_clauses",
        "reason": "maxClauseCount is set to 3932"
      }
    ],
    "type": "search_phase_execution_exception",
    "reason": "all shards failed",
    "phase": "query",
    "grouped": true,
    "failed_shards": [
      {
        "shard": 0,
        "index": ".kibana_alerting_cases_8.12.0_001",
        "node": "xiiv5FWoTyKokEuXkoI49Q",
        "reason": {
          "type": "too_many_clauses",
          "reason": "maxClauseCount is set to 3932"
        }
      }
    ],
    "caused_by": {
      "type": "too_many_clauses",
      "reason": "maxClauseCount is set to 3932",
      "caused_by": {
        "type": "too_many_clauses",
        "reason": "maxClauseCount is set to 3932"
      }
    }
  },
  "status": 500
}

```

Which means too many rules where requested, than ES maxClauseCount could handle

Possible steps to improve:

1. Log error within Kibana server logs (No error log is present now, I was able to see request only turning `      - name: elasticsearch.query` to `debug`)
2. Show more meaningful error to user. Maybe even suggest to select less rules
